+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SBATzGnLHp4bcSjLXsmHfp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the project:\n\n## Complete Project Overview\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .git/                          # Git repository\n├── .thunderdome/                  # Benchmark evaluation configuration\n│   └── rubric.yaml               # Scoring rubric for automated tests\n├── src/                          # Source code directory (empty - .gitkeep only)\n│   └── .gitkeep\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                 # ESLint configuration\n├── .gitignore                    # Git ignore rules\n├── .thunderdome-output.jsonl     # Test output log\n├── .thunderdome-stderr.log       # Test error log\n├── TASK.md                       # Project requirements\n├── package.json                  # Node.js dependencies and scripts\n├── package-lock.json             # Locked dependency versions\n├── schema.sql                    # SQLite database schema\n├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript compiler configuration\n└── vitest.config.ts              # Vitest test runner configuration\n```\n\n### 2. Package.json\n\n**Project Name:** bench-collab-server  \n**Version:** 1.0.0  \n**Type:** ES Module\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` - Compile TypeScript with tsc\n- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint on src/\n- `npm run test` - Run tests with Vitest\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- ws ^8.18.0 (WebSocket library)\n- better-sqlite3 ^11.0.0 (SQLite database)\n- express ^4.21.0 (HTTP server)\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- typescript ^5.4.0\n- vitest ^2.0.0\n- @vitest/coverage-v8 ^2.0.0\n- eslint ^8.56.0\n- @typescript-eslint/parser ^7.0.0\n- @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin ^7.0.0\n- Type definitions for ws, better-sqlite3, express, supertest\n- supertest ^7.0.0 (HTTP testing library)\n\n### 3. tsconfig.json\n\n**Compiler Options:**\n- Target: E