nt:**\n- Entry point: `src/server.ts` or `src/index.ts`\n- Export `createApp` factory function\n- Accepts optional database file path\n- Returns object with:\n  - `app` - Express application\n  - `start(port?)` - Starts listening, returns port (0 = random)\n  - `stop()` - Cleanly shuts down server and connections\n\n### 7. schema.sql - Database Schema\n\n**Tables:**\n1. `documents` - Stores document metadata\n   - id (TEXT PRIMARY KEY)\n   - title (TEXT NOT NULL)\n   - content (TEXT NOT NULL, default '')\n   - created_at, updated_at (timestamps)\n\n2. `versions` - Tracks version history\n   - id (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT)\n   - document_id (FOREIGN KEY references documents)\n   - version (INTEGER)\n   - content (TEXT)\n   - operation (JSON of the operation)\n   - created_at (timestamp)\n   - UNIQUE constraint on (document_id, version)\n\n3. `active_connections` - Tracks active WebSocket connections\n   - id (TEXT PRIMARY KEY)\n   - document_id (FOREIGN KEY references documents)\n   - connected_at (timestamp)\n\n### 8. Testing Rubric (.thunderdome/rubric.yaml)\n\n**Total Points:** 100  \n**Pass Threshold:** 70  \n**Total Tests:** 45\n\n**Scoring Breakdown:**\n- Build (10 pts) - TypeScript compilation\n- Lint (5 pts) - ESLint pass\n- REST CRUD (15 pts) - 10 tests\n- WebSocket Lifecycle (15 pts) - 8 tests\n- Single Client Editing (10 pts) - 6 tests\n- Two-Client Convergence (20 pts) - 8 tests\n- Stress Test (15 pts) - 10 concurrent clients (5 tests)\n- Error Handling (5 pts) - 5 tests\n- Persistence (5 pts) - 3 tests\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a **greenfield collaborative editing server project** with no source code written yet. The infrastructure is fully set up with TypeScript, Express, WebSockets, SQLite, and testing frameworks. The main challenge is implementing Operational Transform or CRDTs for conflict resolution to ensure concurrent edits from multiple clients converge correctly."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa31249 (for resuming to continue this ag