+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Gag3nyGZHJcqF9ovU67zRx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Q1QZG5Gu7QRcePUcmHt8Y3","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-collaborative-editor.md","content":"# Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a collaborative real-time document editing server with REST API, WebSocket collaboration, OT-based conflict resolution, and SQLite persistence.\n\n**Architecture:** Express HTTP server with ws WebSocket server attached to the same HTTP server. OT (Operational Transform) for conflict resolution using position-based insert/delete operations with server-side transformation. SQLite via better-sqlite3 for persistence. Factory function `createApp` exports the server.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Express, ws, better-sqlite3, vitest + supertest for testing\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Database Layer (`src/db.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport { join, dirname } from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __dirname = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nexport function createDatabase(dbPath?: string): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath || ':memory:');\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n  const schema = readFileSync(join(__dirname, '..', 'schema.sql'), 'utf-8');\n  db.exec(schema);\n  return db;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: OT Engine (`src/ot.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ot.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nDefine operation types and the transform function. Operations are either `insert` (position + text) or `delete` (position + count).\n\n```typescript\nexport interface InsertOp {\n  type: 'insert';\n  position: number;\n  text: string;\n}\n\nexport interface DeleteOp {\n  type: 'delete';\n  position: number;\n  count: number;\n}\n\nexport type Operation = InsertOp | DeleteOp;\n\n// Apply an operation to a document string\nexport function applyOp(doc: string, op: Operation): string {\n  if (op.type === 'insert') {\n    if (op.position < 0 || op.position > doc.length) {\n      throw new Error(`Insert position ${op.position} out of bounds for document length ${doc.length}`);\n    }\n    return doc.slice(0, op.position) + op.text + doc.slice(op.position);\n  } else {\n    if (op.position < 0 || op.position + op.count > doc.length) {\n      throw new Error(`Delete range [${op.position}, ${op.position + op.count}) out of bounds for document length ${doc.length}`);\n    }\n    return doc.slice(0, op.position) + doc.slice(op.position + op.count);\n  }\n}\n\n// Transform op1 against op2 (both concurrent).\n// Returns transformed op1 that can be applied after op2.\nexport function transformOp(op1: Operation, op2: Operation): Operation {\n  if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n    if (op1.position <= op2.position) {\n      return op1; // op1 inserts before or at same position, no change\n    } else {\n      return { ...op1, position: op1.position + op2.text.length };\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'delete') {\n    if (op1.position <= op2.position) {\n      return op1;\n    } else if (op1.position >= op2.position + op2.count) {\n      return { ...op1, position: op1.position - op2.count };\n    } else {\n      // Insert is within deleted range - move to delete position\n      return { ...op1, position: op2.position };\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n    if (op2.position <= op1.position) {\n      return { ...op1, position: op1.position + op2.text.length };\n    } else if (op2.position >= op1.position + op1.count) {\n      return op1;\n    } else {\n      // Insert is within our delete range - expand delete to account for inserted text\n      return { ...op1, count: op1.count + op2.text.length };\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Both deletes\n  if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'delete') {\n    if (op1.position >= op2.position + op2.count) {\n      return { ...op1, position: op1.position - op2.count };\n    } else if (op2.position >= op1.position + op1.count) {\n      return op1;\n    } else {\n      // Overlapping deletes\n      const start1 = op1.position;\n      const end1 = op1.position + op1.count;\n      const start2 = op2.position;\n      const end2 = op2.position + op2.count;\n\n      const newStart = Math.min(start1, start2);\n      const overlapStart = Math.max(start1, start2);\n      const overlapEnd = Math.min(end1, end2);\n      const overlap = Math.max(0, overlapEnd - overlapStart);\n\n      const newPosition = start1 <= start2 ? start1 : start1 - (overlapStart - start2);\n      const newCount = op1.count - overlap;\n\n      if (newCount <= 0) {\n        return { type: 'delete', position: newPosition, count: 0 };\n      }\n\n      return { type: 'delete', position: newPosition, count: newCount };\n    }\n  }\n\n  return op1;\n}\n\n// Validate that an operation is well-formed\nexport function validateOp(op: unknown): op is Operation {\n  if (!op || typeof op !== 'object') return false;\n  const o = op as Record<string, unknown>;\n  if (o.type === 'insert') {\n    return typeof o.position === 'number' && typeof o.text === 'string' && o.position >= 0;\n  }\n  if (o.type === 'delete') {\n    return typeof o.position === 'number' && typeof o.count === 'number' && o.position >= 0 && o.count >= 0;\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Document Routes (`src/routes.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nREST API for CRUD + version history.\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // List all documents\n  router.get('/documents', (_req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const docs = db.prepare('SELECT id, title, content, created_at, updated_at FROM documents ORDER BY updated_at DESC').all();\n    res.json(docs);\n  });\n\n  // Create a document\n  router.post('/documents', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const { title, content } = req.body;\n    if (!title || typeof title !== 'string') {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'title is required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = randomUUID();\n    const docContent = typeof content === 'string' ? content : '';\n    db.prepare('INSERT INTO documents (id, title, content) VALUES (?, ?, ?)').run(id, title, docContent);\n    // Create initial version\n    db.prepare('INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation) VALUES (?, 1, ?, NULL)').run(id, docContent);\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(id);\n    res.status(201).json(doc);\n  });\n\n  // Get a document\n  router.get('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json(doc);\n  });\n\n  // Update a document\n  router.put('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const { title, content } = req.body;\n    if (title !== undefined) {\n      db.prepare(\"UPDATE documents SET title = ?, updated_at = datetime('now') WHERE id = ?\").run(title, req.params.id);\n    }\n    if (content !== undefined) {\n      db.prepare(\"UPDATE documents SET content = ?, updated_at = datetime('now') WHERE id = ?\").run(content, req.params.id);\n    }\n    const updated = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    res.json(updated);\n  });\n\n  // Delete a document\n  router.delete('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    db.prepare('DELETE FROM documents WHERE id = ?').run(req.params.id);\n    res.status(204).send();\n  });\n\n  // Get version history\n  router.get('/documents/:id/versions', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const versions = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM versions WHERE document_id = ? ORDER BY version ASC').all(req.params.id);\n    res.json(versions);\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: WebSocket Handler (`src/ws.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ws.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nManages WebSocket connections per document, applies OT, broadcasts changes.\n\n```typescript\nimport { WebSocketServer, WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport { IncomingMessage } from 'http';\nimport { Server } from 'http';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\nimport { Operation, applyOp, transformOp, validateOp } from './ot.js';\n\ninterface Client {\n  ws: WebSocket;\n  id: string;\n  documentId: string;\n}\n\ninterface DocumentState {\n  version: number;\n  clients: Set<Client>;\n}\n\nexport function setupWebSocket(server: Server, db: Database.Database) {\n  const wss = new WebSocketServer({ noServer: true });\n  const documents = new Map<string, DocumentState>();\n\n  function getOrCreateDocState(docId: string): DocumentState {\n    let state = documents.get(docId);\n    if (!state) {\n      // Get current version from DB\n      const row = db.prepare('SELECT MAX(version) as maxVersion FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?').get(docId) as { maxVersion: number | null } | undefined;\n      state = { version: row?.maxVersion || 1, clients: new Set() };\n      documents.set(docId, state);\n    }\n    return state;\n  }\n\n  server.on('upgrade', (request: IncomingMessage, socket, head) => {\n    const url = new URL(request.url || '', `http://${request.headers.host}`);\n    const match = url.pathname.match(/^\\/documents\\/([^/]+)\\/ws$/);\n\n    if (!match) {\n      socket.destroy();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const docId = match[1];\n\n    // Verify document exists\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(docId);\n    if (!doc) {\n      socket.write('HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n      socket.destroy();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    wss.handleUpgrade(request, socket, head, (ws) => {\n      wss.emit('connection', ws, request, docId);\n    });\n  });\n\n  wss.on('connection', (ws: WebSocket, _request: IncomingMessage, docId: string) => {\n    const clientId = randomUUID();\n    const client: Client = { ws, id: clientId, documentId: docId };\n    const state = getOrCreateDocState(docId);\n    state.clients.add(client);\n\n    // Send current document state\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(docId) as { id: string; content: string; title: string } | undefined;\n    if (doc) {\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'sync',\n        content: doc.content,\n        version: state.version,\n        clientId,\n      }));\n    }\n\n    ws.on('message', (data) => {\n      try {\n        const message = JSON.parse(data.toString());\n\n        if (message.type === 'operation') {\n          const op = message.operation;\n          if (!validateOp(op)) {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Invalid operation' }));\n            return;\n          }\n\n          const clientVersion = typeof message.version === 'number' ? message.version : state.version;\n\n          // Get current doc content\n          const currentDoc = db.prepare('SELECT content FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(docId) as { content: string } | undefined;\n          if (!currentDoc) {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Document not found' }));\n            return;\n          }\n\n          // Transform against any operations that happened since client's version\n          let transformedOp: Operation = op;\n          if (clientVersion < state.version) {\n            const missedOps = db.prepare(\n              'SELECT operation FROM versions WHERE document_id = ? AND version > ? AND version <= ? ORDER BY version ASC'\n            ).all(docId, clientVersion, state.version) as { operation: string }[];\n\n            for (const row of missedOps) {\n              if (row.operation) {\n                const serverOp = JSON.parse(row.operation) as Operation;\n                transformedOp = transformOp(transformedOp, serverOp);\n              }\n            }\n          }\n\n          // Apply transformed operation\n          let newContent: string;\n          try {\n            // Handle no-op deletes\n            if (transformedOp.type === 'delete' && transformedOp.count === 0) {\n              ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n                type: 'ack',\n                version: state.version,\n              }));\n              return;\n            }\n            newContent = applyOp(currentDoc.content, transformedOp);\n          } catch (err) {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: (err as Error).message }));\n            return;\n          }\n\n          state.version++;\n          const newVersion = state.version;\n\n          // Persist\n          db.prepare(\"UPDATE documents SET content = ?, updated_at = datetime('now') WHERE id = ?\").run(newContent, docId);\n          db.prepare('INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)').run(\n            docId, newVersion, newContent, JSON.stringify(transformedOp)\n          );\n\n          // Ack to sender\n          ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n            type: 'ack',\n            version: newVersion,\n          }));\n\n          // Broadcast to others\n          for (const c of state.clients) {\n            if (c.ws !== ws && c.ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n              c.ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n                type: 'operation',\n                operation: transformedOp,\n                version: newVersion,\n                clientId,\n              }));\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      } catch {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Invalid message format' }));\n      }\n    });\n\n    ws.on('close', () => {\n      state.clients.delete(client);\n      if (state.clients.size === 0) {\n        documents.delete(docId);\n      }\n    });\n  });\n\n  return wss;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Server Entry Point (`src/server.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/server.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createServer, Server } from 'http';\nimport { WebSocketServer } from 'ws';\nimport { createDatabase } from './db.js';\nimport { createRouter } from './routes.js';\nimport { setupWebSocket } from './ws.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface AppInstance {\n  app: express.Express;\n  start: (port?: number) => Promise<number>;\n  stop: () => Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): AppInstance {\n  const db: Database.Database = createDatabase(dbPath);\n  const app = express();\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const router = createRouter(db);\n  app.use(router);\n\n  const server: Server = createServer(app);\n  const wss = setupWebSocket(server, db);\n\n  let started = false;\n\n  async function start(port?: number): Promise<number> {\n    return new Promise((resolve) => {\n      server.listen(port || 0, () => {\n        started = true;\n        const addr = server.address();\n        const actualPort = typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : 0;\n        resolve(actualPort);\n      });\n    });\n  }\n\n  async function stop(): Promise<void> {\n    // Close all WebSocket connections\n    wss.clients.forEach((client) => {\n      client.close();\n    });\n\n    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n      if (!started) {\n        db.close();\n        resolve();\n        return;\n      }\n      server.close((err) => {\n        db.close();\n        if (err) reject(err);\n        else resolve();\n      });\n    });\n  }\n\n  return { app, start, stop };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Tests (`src/tests/`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `tests/api.test.ts`\n- Create: `tests/ws.test.ts`\n- Create: `tests/ot.test.ts`\n\nWrite tests covering REST API, WebSocket lifecycle, OT transforms, concurrent editing, persistence, and error handling.\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Build, Lint, Test\n\nRun `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, `npm run test` and fix any issues.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":120,"cache_read_input_tokens":22088,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":120},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eff942b0-f05c-449c-b23b-f2987a63273c","uuid":"a7a01bb3-16f3-4e45-bd75-23361783dbf9"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q1QZG5Gu7QRcePUcmHt8Y3","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-collaborative-editor.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eff942b0-f05c-449c-b23b-f2987a63273c","uuid":"cd1f791c-c13b-464b-a5e2-4c8dce58169b","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-collaborative-editor.md","content":"# Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a collaborative real-time document editing server with REST API, WebSocket collaboration, OT-based conflict resolution, and SQLite persistence.\n\n**Architecture:** Express HTTP server with ws WebSocket server attached to the same HTTP server. OT (Operational Transform) for conflict resolution using position-based insert/delete operations with server-side transformation. SQLite via better-sqlite3 for persistence. Factory function `createApp` exports the server.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Express, ws, better-sqlite3, vitest + supertest for testing\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Database Layer (`src/db.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport { join, dirname } from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __dirname = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nexport function createDatabase(dbPath?: string): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath || ':memory:');\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n  const schema = readFileSync(join(__dirname, '..', 'schema.sql'), 'utf-8');\n  db.exec(schema);\n  return db;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: OT Engine (`src/ot.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ot.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nDefine operation types and the transform function. Operations are either `insert` (position + text) or `delete` (position + count).\n\n```typescript\nexport interface InsertOp {\n  type: 'insert';\n  position: number;\n  text: string;\n}\n\nexport interface DeleteOp {\n  type: 'delete';\n  position: number;\n  count: number;\n}\n\nexport type Operation = InsertOp | DeleteOp;\n\n// Apply an operation to a document string\nexport function applyOp(doc: string, op: Operation): string {\n  if (op.type === 'insert') {\n    if (op.position < 0 || op.position > doc.length) {\n      throw new Error(`Insert position ${op.position} out of bounds for document length ${doc.length}`);\n    }\n    return doc.slice(0, op.position) + op.text + doc.slice(op.position);\n  } else {\n    if (op.position < 0 || op.position + op.count > doc.length) {\n      throw new Error(`Delete range [${op.position}, ${op.position + op.count}) out of bounds for document length ${doc.length}`);\n    }\n    return doc.slice(0, op.position) + doc.slice(op.position + op.count);\n  }\n}\n\n// Transform op1 against op2 (both concurrent).\n// Returns transformed op1 that can be applied after op2.\nexport function transformOp(op1: Operation, op2: Operation): Operation {\n  if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n    if (op1.position <= op2.position) {\n      return op1; // op1 inserts before or at same position, no change\n    } else {\n      return { ...op1, position: op1.position + op2.text.length };\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'delete') {\n    if (op1.position <= op2.position) {\n      return op1;\n    } else if (op1.position >= op2.position + op2.count) {\n      return { ...op1, position: op1.position - op2.count };\n    } else {\n      // Insert is within deleted range - move to delete position\n      return { ...op1, position: op2.position };\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n    if (op2.position <= op1.position) {\n      return { ...op1, position: op1.position + op2.text.length };\n    } else if (op2.position >= op1.position + op1.count) {\n      return op1;\n    } else {\n      // Insert is within our delete range - expand delete to account for inserted text\n      return { ...op1, count: op1.count + op2.text.length };\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Both deletes\n  if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'delete') {\n    if (op1.position >= op2.position + op2.count) {\n      return { ...op1, position: op1.position - op2.count };\n    } else if (op2.position >= op1.position + op1.count) {\n      return op1;\n    } else {\n      // Overlapping deletes\n      const start1 = op1.position;\n      const end1 = op1.position + op1.count;\n      const start2 = op2.position;\n      const end2 = op2.position + op2.count;\n\n      const newStart = Math.min(start1, start2);\n      const overlapStart = Math.max(start1, start2);\n      const overlapEnd = Math.min(end1, end2);\n      const overlap = Math.max(0, overlapEnd - overlapStart);\n\n      const newPosition = start1 <= start2 ? start1 : start1 - (overlapStart - start2);\n      const newCount = op1.count - overlap;\n\n      if (newCount <= 0) {\n        return { type: 'delete', position: newPosition, count: 0 };\n      }\n\n      return { type: 'delete', position: newPosition, count: newCount };\n    }\n  }\n\n  return op1;\n}\n\n// Validate that an operation is well-formed\nexport function validateOp(op: unknown): op is Operation {\n  if (!op || typeof op !== 'object') return false;\n  const o = op as Record<string, unknown>;\n  if (o.type === 'insert') {\n    return typeof o.position === 'number' && typeof o.text === 'string' && o.position >= 0;\n  }\n  if (o.type === 'delete') {\n    return typeof o.position === 'number' && typeof o.count === 'number' && o.position >= 0 && o.count >= 0;\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Document Routes (`src/routes.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/routes.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nREST API for CRUD + version history.\n\n```typescript\nimport { Router, Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createRouter(db: Database.Database): Router {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  // List all documents\n  router.get('/documents', (_req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const docs = db.prepare('SELECT id, title, content, created_at, updated_at FROM documents ORDER BY updated_at DESC').all();\n    res.json(docs);\n  });\n\n  // Create a document\n  router.post('/documents', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const { title, content } = req.body;\n    if (!title || typeof title !== 'string') {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'title is required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const id = randomUUID();\n    const docContent = typeof content === 'string' ? content : '';\n    db.prepare('INSERT INTO documents (id, title, content) VALUES (?, ?, ?)').run(id, title, docContent);\n    // Create initial version\n    db.prepare('INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation) VALUES (?, 1, ?, NULL)').run(id, docContent);\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(id);\n    res.status(201).json(doc);\n  });\n\n  // Get a document\n  router.get('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    res.json(doc);\n  });\n\n  // Update a document\n  router.put('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const { title, content } = req.body;\n    if (title !== undefined) {\n      db.prepare(\"UPDATE documents SET title = ?, updated_at = datetime('now') WHERE id = ?\").run(title, req.params.id);\n    }\n    if (content !== undefined) {\n      db.prepare(\"UPDATE documents SET content = ?, updated_at = datetime('now') WHERE id = ?\").run(content, req.params.id);\n    }\n    const updated = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    res.json(updated);\n  });\n\n  // Delete a document\n  router.delete('/documents/:id', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    db.prepare('DELETE FROM documents WHERE id = ?').run(req.params.id);\n    res.status(204).send();\n  });\n\n  // Get version history\n  router.get('/documents/:id/versions', (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) {\n      res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const versions = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM versions WHERE document_id = ? ORDER BY version ASC').all(req.params.id);\n    res.json(versions);\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: WebSocket Handler (`src/ws.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ws.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\nManages WebSocket connections per document, applies OT, broadcasts changes.\n\n```typescript\nimport { WebSocketServer, WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport { IncomingMessage } from 'http';\nimport { Server } from 'http';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\nimport { Operation, applyOp, transformOp, validateOp } from './ot.js';\n\ninterface Client {\n  ws: WebSocket;\n  id: string;\n  documentId: string;\n}\n\ninterface DocumentState {\n  version: number;\n  clients: Set<Client>;\n}\n\nexport function setupWebSocket(server: Server, db: Database.Database) {\n  const wss = new WebSocketServer({ noServer: true });\n  const documents = new Map<string, DocumentState>();\n\n  function getOrCreateDocState(docId: string): DocumentState {\n    let state = documents.get(docId);\n    if (!state) {\n      // Get current version from DB\n      const row = db.prepare('SELECT MAX(version) as maxVersion FROM versions WHERE document_id = ?').get(docId) as { maxVersion: number | null } | undefined;\n      state = { version: row?.maxVersion || 1, clients: new Set() };\n      documents.set(docId, state);\n    }\n    return state;\n  }\n\n  server.on('upgrade', (request: IncomingMessage, socket, head) => {\n    const url = new URL(request.url || '', `http://${request.headers.host}`);\n    const match = url.pathname.match(/^\\/documents\\/([^/]+)\\/ws$/);\n\n    if (!match) {\n      socket.destroy();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const docId = match[1];\n\n    // Verify document exists\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(docId);\n    if (!doc) {\n      socket.write('HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n      socket.destroy();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    wss.handleUpgrade(request, socket, head, (ws) => {\n      wss.emit('connection', ws, request, docId);\n    });\n  });\n\n  wss.on('connection', (ws: WebSocket, _request: IncomingMessage, docId: string) => {\n    const clientId = randomUUID();\n    const client: Client = { ws, id: clientId, documentId: docId };\n    const state = getOrCreateDocState(docId);\n    state.clients.add(client);\n\n    // Send current document state\n    const doc = db.prepare('SELECT * FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(docId) as { id: string; content: string; title: string } | undefined;\n    if (doc) {\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'sync',\n        content: doc.content,\n        version: state.version,\n        clientId,\n      }));\n    }\n\n    ws.on('message', (data) => {\n      try {\n        const message = JSON.parse(data.toString());\n\n        if (message.type === 'operation') {\n          const op = message.operation;\n          if (!validateOp(op)) {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Invalid operation' }));\n            return;\n          }\n\n          const clientVersion = typeof message.version === 'number' ? message.version : state.version;\n\n          // Get current doc content\n          const currentDoc = db.prepare('SELECT content FROM documents WHERE id = ?').get(docId) as { content: string } | undefined;\n          if (!currentDoc) {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Document not found' }));\n            return;\n          }\n\n          // Transform against any operations that happened since client's version\n          let transformedOp: Operation = op;\n          if (clientVersion < state.version) {\n            const missedOps = db.prepare(\n              'SELECT operation FROM versions WHERE document_id = ? AND version > ? AND version <= ? ORDER BY version ASC'\n            ).all(docId, clientVersion, state.version) as { operation: string }[];\n\n            for (const row of missedOps) {\n              if (row.operation) {\n                const serverOp = JSON.parse(row.operation) as Operation;\n                transformedOp = transformOp(transformedOp, serverOp);\n              }\n            }\n          }\n\n          // Apply transformed operation\n          let newContent: string;\n          try {\n            // Handle no-op deletes\n            if (transformedOp.type === 'delete' && transformedOp.count === 0) {\n              ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n                type: 'ack',\n                version: state.version,\n              }));\n              return;\n            }\n            newContent = applyOp(currentDoc.content, transformedOp);\n          } catch (err) {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: (err as Error).message }));\n            return;\n          }\n\n          state.version++;\n          const newVersion = state.version;\n\n          // Persist\n          db.prepare(\"UPDATE documents SET content = ?, updated_at = datetime('now') WHERE id = ?\").run(newContent, docId);\n          db.prepare('INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)').run(\n            docId, newVersion, newContent, JSON.stringify(transformedOp)\n          );\n\n          // Ack to sender\n          ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n            type: 'ack',\n            version: newVersion,\n          }));\n\n          // Broadcast to others\n          for (const c of state.clients) {\n            if (c.ws !== ws && c.ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n              c.ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n                type: 'operation',\n                operation: transformedOp,\n                version: newVersion,\n                clientId,\n              }));\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      } catch {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Invalid message format' }));\n      }\n    });\n\n    ws.on('close', () => {\n      state.clients.delete(client);\n      if (state.clients.size === 0) {\n        documents.delete(docId);\n      }\n    });\n  });\n\n  return wss;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Server Entry Point (`src/server.ts`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/server.ts`\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createServer, Server } from 'http';\nimport { WebSocketServer } from 'ws';\nimport { createDatabase } from './db.js';\nimport { createRouter } from './routes.js';\nimport { setupWebSocket } from './ws.js';\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport interface AppInstance {\n  app: express.Express;\n  start: (port?: number) => Promise<number>;\n  stop: () => Promise<void>;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): AppInstance {\n  const db: Database.Database = createDatabase(dbPath);\n  const app = express();\n  app.use(express.json());\n\n  const router = createRouter(db);\n  app.use(router);\n\n  const server: Server = createServer(app);\n  const wss = setupWebSocket(server, db);\n\n  let started = false;\n\n  async function start(port?: number): Promise<number> {\n    return new Promise((resolve) => {\n      server.listen(port || 0, () => {\n        started = true;\n        const addr = server.address();\n        const actualPort = typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : 0;\n        resolve(actualPort);\n      });\n    });\n  }\n\n  async function stop(): Promise<void> {\n    // Close all WebSocket connections\n    wss.clients.forEach((client) => {\n      client.close();\n    });\n\n    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n      if (!started) {\n        db.close();\n        resolve();\n        return;\n      }\n      server.close((err) => {\n        db.close();\n        if (err) reject(err);\n        else resolve();\n      });\n    });\n  }\n\n  return { app, start, stop };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Tests (`src/tests/`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `tests/api.test.ts`\n- Create: `tests/ws.test.ts`\n- Create: `tests/ot.test.ts`\n\nWrite tests covering REST API, WebSocket lifecycle, OT transforms, concurrent editing, persistence, and error handling.\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Build, Lint, Test\n\nRun `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, `npm run test` and fix any issues.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
